    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-07-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="701"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d701">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No 10044/26.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-07-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1908</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Sultan, yielding to the demand for reforms, has proclaimed the constitution,
                    which had lapsed for 30 years, and imperial orders have been sent to all the
                    governors throughout the Empire with a view to proceeding to the election of
                    parliamentary representatives Comparative tranquility prevails, but considerable
                    anxiety exists regarding final outcome.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leishman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
